File: e-Commerce sites are no longer limited to what physical stores can sell. JOHANNESBURG - Online shops may now sell anything except alcohol and tobacco products. That's according to new regulations published by government. READ: Level 4 lockdown: Govt gazettes winter clothing list That means e-commerce sites are no longer limited to what physical stores can sell. There are however stringent measures to prevent the spread of COVID-19  that will need to be followed by retailers and courier companies. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Online shopping now allowed by eNCA.com on Scribd 